 170/// <summary>
 171/// Aggregates knowledge from all registered knowledge sources.
 172/// Provides a unified view of all system knowledge for AI consumption.
 173/// </summary>
 174public sealed class KnowledgeAggregator : IDisposable
 175{
 176    private readonly ConcurrentDictionary<string, IKnowledgeSource> _sources = new(StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase);
 177    private readonly ConcurrentDictionary<string, CachedKnowledge> _cache = new(StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase);
 178    private readonly SemaphoreSlim _aggregationLock = new(1, 1);
 179    private readonly TimeSpan _cacheExpiration = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5);
 180    private bool _disposed;
 181
 182    /// <summary>
 183    /// Event raised when knowledge changes in any source.
 184    /// </summary>
 185    public event EventHandler<KnowledgeChangedEventArgs>? KnowledgeChanged;
 186
 187    /// <summary>
 188    /// Gets all aggregated knowledge from all sources.
 189    /// </summary>
 190    /// <param name="ct">Cancellation token.</param>
 191    /// <returns>Aggregated knowledge from all sources.</returns>
 192    public async Task<AggregatedKnowledge> GetAllKnowledgeAsync(CancellationToken ct = default)
 193    {
 194        await _aggregationLock.WaitAsync(ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 195        try
 196        {
 197            var allKnowledge = new List<KnowledgeObject>();
 198            var bySource = new Dictionary<string, IReadOnlyCollection<KnowledgeObject>>();
 199            var byTopic = new Dictionary<string, List<KnowledgeObject>>();
 200            var allCapabilities = new List<KnowledgeCapability>();
 201            var availableCount = 0;
 202
 203            foreach (var source in _sources.Values)
 204            {
 205                if (!source.IsAvailable)
 206                    continue;
 207
 208                availableCount++;
 209
 210                try
 211                {
 212                    var sourceKnowledge = await GetSourceKnowledgeAsync(source, ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 213                    allKnowledge.AddRange(sourceKnowledge);
 214                    bySource[source.SourceId] = sourceKnowledge.ToArray();
 215
 216                    foreach (var knowledge in sourceKnowledge)
 217                    {
 218                        if (!byTopic.TryGetValue(knowledge.Topic, out var topicList))
 219                        {
 220                            topicList = new List<KnowledgeObject>();
 221                            byTopic[knowledge.Topic] = topicList;
 222                        }
 223                        topicList.Add(knowledge);
 224                    }
 225
 226                    allCapabilities.AddRange(source.Capabilities);
 227                }
 228                catch (OperationCanceledException)
 229                {
 230                    throw;
 231                }
 232                catch
 233                {
 234                    // Source failed, skip but continue with others
 235                }
 236            }
 237
 238            return new AggregatedKnowledge
 239            {
 240                AllKnowledge = allKnowledge,
 241                BySource = bySource,
 242                ByTopic = byTopic.ToDictionary(kvp => kvp.Key, kvp => (IReadOnlyCollection<KnowledgeObject>)kvp.Value.As
 243                AllCapabilities = allCapabilities,
 244                SourceCount = _sources.Count,
 245                AvailableSourceCount = availableCount
 246            };
 247        }
 248        finally
 249        {
 250            _aggregationLock.Release();
 251        }
 252    }
 253
 254    /// <summary>
 255    /// Registers a knowledge source.
 256    /// </summary>
 257    /// <param name="source">The knowledge source to register.</param>
 258    /// <param name="ct">Cancellation token.</param>
 259    public async Task RegisterSourceAsync(IKnowledgeSource source, CancellationToken ct = default)
 260    {
 261        ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(source);
 262
 263        _sources[source.SourceId] = source;
 264        _cache.TryRemove(source.SourceId, out _);
 265
 266        // Pre-warm the cache
 267        await GetSourceKnowledgeAsync(source, ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 268
 269        OnKnowledgeChanged(new KnowledgeChangedEventArgs
 270        {
 271            SourceId = source.SourceId,
 272            ChangeType = KnowledgeChangeType.SourceAvailable
 273        });
 274    }
 275
 276    /// <summary>
 277    /// Unregisters a knowledge source.
 278    /// </summary>
 279    /// <param name="sourceId">The ID of the source to unregister.</param>
 280    /// <param name="ct">Cancellation token.</param>
 281    public Task UnregisterSourceAsync(string sourceId, CancellationToken ct = default)
 282    {
 283        ArgumentException.ThrowIfNullOrEmpty(sourceId);
 284
 285        if (_sources.TryRemove(sourceId, out _))
 286        {
 287            _cache.TryRemove(sourceId, out _);
 288
 289            OnKnowledgeChanged(new KnowledgeChangedEventArgs
 290            {
 291                SourceId = sourceId,
 292                ChangeType = KnowledgeChangeType.SourceUnavailable
 293            });
 294        }
 295
 296        return Task.CompletedTask;
 297    }

 336    private async Task<IReadOnlyCollection<KnowledgeObject>> GetSourceKnowledgeAsync(IKnowledgeSource source, Cancellati
 337    {
 338        if (_cache.TryGetValue(source.SourceId, out var cached) && !cached.IsExpired(_cacheExpiration))
 339        {
 340            return cached.Knowledge;
 341        }
 342
 343        var staticKnowledge = await source.GetStaticKnowledgeAsync(ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 344        var dynamicKnowledge = await source.GetDynamicKnowledgeAsync(ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 345
 346        var allKnowledge = staticKnowledge.Concat(dynamicKnowledge).ToArray();
 347
 348        _cache[source.SourceId] = new CachedKnowledge
 349        {
 350            Knowledge = allKnowledge,
 351            CachedAt = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow
 352        };
 353
 354        return allKnowledge;
 355    }

 402    /// <summary>
 403    /// Scans for all plugins that implement IKnowledgeSource.
 404    /// </summary>
 405    /// <param name="ct">Cancellation token.</param>
 406    /// <returns>Collection of knowledge sources from plugins.</returns>
 407    public Task<IEnumerable<IKnowledgeSource>> ScanAsync(CancellationToken ct = default)
 408    {
 409        var sources = new List<IKnowledgeSource>();
 410
 411        if (_kernelContext == null)
 412        {
 413            return Task.FromResult<IEnumerable<IKnowledgeSource>>(sources);
 414        }
 415
 416        // Get all plugins
 417        var plugins = _kernelContext.GetPlugins<IPlugin>();
 418
 419        foreach (var plugin in plugins)
 420        {
 421            ct.ThrowIfCancellationRequested();
 422
 423            // Check if plugin directly implements IKnowledgeSource
 424            if (plugin is IKnowledgeSource directSource)
 425            {
 426                sources.Add(directSource);
 427                continue;
 428            }
 429
 430            // Check if plugin can provide knowledge through PluginBase
 431            if (plugin is PluginBase pluginBase)
 432            {
 433                var wrapper = new PluginKnowledgeSourceWrapper(pluginBase);
 434                if (wrapper.Capabilities.Count > 0)
 435                {
 436                    sources.Add(wrapper);
 437                }
 438            }
 439        }
 440
 441        return Task.FromResult<IEnumerable<IKnowledgeSource>>(sources);
 442    }
 443
 444    /// <summary>
 445    /// Checks if a plugin is knowledge-aware.
 446    /// </summary>
 447    /// <param name="plugin">The plugin to check.</param>
 448    /// <param name="ct">Cancellation token.</param>
 449    /// <returns>True if the plugin can provide knowledge.</returns>
 450    public Task<bool> IsKnowledgeAwareAsync(IPlugin plugin, CancellationToken ct = default)
 451    {

 453
 454        // Direct implementation
 455        if (plugin is IKnowledgeSource)
 456            return Task.FromResult(true);
 457
 458        // PluginBase with registration knowledge
 459        if (plugin is PluginBase pluginBase)
 460        {
 461            var knowledge = pluginBase.GetRegistrationKnowledge();

 463        }

 465        return Task.FromResult(false);
 466    }

 468    /// <summary>

 473    public IEnumerable<KnowledgeCapability> ExtractCapabilities(IPlugin plugin)
 474    {
 475        ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(plugin);
 476
 477        if (plugin is IKnowledgeSource source)
 478        {
 479            return source.Capabilities;
 480        }
 481
 482        if (plugin is PluginBase pluginBase)
 483        {
 484            var knowledge = pluginBase.GetRegistrationKnowledge();
 485            if (knowledge != null && knowledge.Payload.TryGetValue("operations", out var ops) && ops is string[] operati
 486            {
 487                return operations.Select(op => new KnowledgeCapability
 488                {
 489                    CapabilityId = $"{plugin.Id}.{op}",
 490                    Description = $"Operation: {op}"
 491                });
 492            }
 493        }
 494
 495        return Enumerable.Empty<KnowledgeCapability>();
 496    }

 533            var request = new SdkKnowledgeRequest
 534            {

 536                RequestorPluginId = "knowledge-system",
 537                Topic = query.TopicPattern ?? "*",
 538                QueryParameters = new Dictionary<string, object>

 541                }

 543

 572#region Hot Reload Handler
 573
 574/// <summary>
 575/// Handles plugin load/unload events for dynamic knowledge updates.
 576/// </summary>
 577public sealed class HotReloadHandler : IDisposable
 578{
 579    private readonly KnowledgeAggregator _aggregator;
 580    private readonly PluginScanner _scanner;
 581    private readonly IMessageBus? _messageBus;
 582    private readonly List<IDisposable> _subscriptions = new();
 583    private bool _disposed;
 584
 585    /// <summary>
 586    /// Creates a new hot reload handler.
 587    /// </summary>
 588    /// <param name="aggregator">The knowledge aggregator.</param>
 589    /// <param name="scanner">The plugin scanner.</param>
 590    /// <param name="messageBus">Optional message bus for plugin lifecycle events.</param>
 591    public HotReloadHandler(KnowledgeAggregator aggregator, PluginScanner scanner, IMessageBus? messageBus = null)
 592    {
 593        _aggregator = aggregator ?? throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(aggregator));
 594        _scanner = scanner ?? throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(scanner));
 595        _messageBus = messageBus;
 596
 597        SubscribeToPluginEvents();
 598    }
 599
 600    /// <summary>
 601    /// Handles a plugin being loaded.
 602    /// </summary>
 603    /// <param name="plugin">The loaded plugin.</param>
 604    /// <param name="ct">Cancellation token.</param>
 605    public async Task OnPluginLoadedAsync(IPlugin plugin, CancellationToken ct = default)
 606    {
 607        ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(plugin);
 608
 609        if (!await _scanner.IsKnowledgeAwareAsync(plugin, ct).ConfigureAwait(false))
 610            return;
 611
 612        if (plugin is IKnowledgeSource source)
 613        {
 614            await _aggregator.RegisterSourceAsync(source, ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 615        }
 616        else if (plugin is PluginBase pluginBase)
 617        {
 618            var wrapper = new PluginBaseKnowledgeSource(pluginBase);
 619            await _aggregator.RegisterSourceAsync(wrapper, ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 620        }
 621    }
 622
 623    /// <summary>
 624    /// Handles a plugin being unloaded.
 625    /// </summary>
 626    /// <param name="pluginId">The ID of the unloaded plugin.</param>
 627    /// <param name="ct">Cancellation token.</param>
 628    public async Task OnPluginUnloadedAsync(string pluginId, CancellationToken ct = default)
 629    {
 630        ArgumentException.ThrowIfNullOrEmpty(pluginId);
 631
 632        await _aggregator.UnregisterSourceAsync(pluginId, ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 633    }
 634
 635    private void SubscribeToPluginEvents()
 636    {
 637        if (_messageBus == null) return;
 638
 639        var loadSub = _messageBus.Subscribe(MessageTopics.PluginLoaded, async message =>
 640        {
 641            if (message.Payload.TryGetValue("plugin", out var pluginObj) && pluginObj is IPlugin plugin)
 642            {
 643                await OnPluginLoadedAsync(plugin).ConfigureAwait(false);
 644            }
 645        });
 646        _subscriptions.Add(loadSub);
 647
 648        var unloadSub = _messageBus.Subscribe(MessageTopics.PluginUnloaded, async message =>
 649        {
 650            if (message.Payload.TryGetValue("pluginId", out var idObj) && idObj is string pluginId)
 651            {
 652                await OnPluginUnloadedAsync(pluginId).ConfigureAwait(false);
 653            }
 654        });
 655        _subscriptions.Add(unloadSub);
 656    }
 657
 658    /// <inheritdoc />
 659    public void Dispose()
 660    {
 661        if (_disposed) return;
 662        _disposed = true;
 663
 664        foreach (var sub in _subscriptions)
 665        {
 666            try { sub.Dispose(); } catch { /* ignore */ }
 667        }
 668        _subscriptions.Clear();
 669    }
 670
 671    /// <summary>

 682        public bool IsAvailable => true;
 683
 684        public IReadOnlyCollection<KnowledgeCapability> Capabilities

 692                    {

 695                    }).ToArray();
 696                }
 697                return Array.Empty<KnowledgeCapability>();
 698            }
 699        }
 700
 701        public Task<IReadOnlyCollection<KnowledgeObject>> GetStaticKnowledgeAsync(CancellationToken ct = default)

 704            return Task.FromResult<IReadOnlyCollection<KnowledgeObject>>(

 706        }

 724/// <summary>
 725/// Tracks what capabilities each plugin provides for efficient lookup.
 726/// </summary>
 727public sealed class CapabilityMatrix
 728{
 729    private readonly ConcurrentDictionary<string, HashSet<KnowledgeCapability>> _matrix = new(StringComparer.OrdinalIgno
 730    private readonly ConcurrentDictionary<string, HashSet<string>> _capabilityToPlugins = new(StringComparer.OrdinalIgno
 731    private readonly object _updateLock = new();
 732
 733    /// <summary>
 734    /// Gets the capabilities for a specific plugin.
 735    /// </summary>
 736    /// <param name="pluginId">The plugin ID.</param>
 737    /// <returns>Array of capabilities.</returns>
 738    public KnowledgeCapability[] GetCapabilities(string pluginId)
 739    {
 740        ArgumentException.ThrowIfNullOrEmpty(pluginId);
 741
 742        return _matrix.TryGetValue(pluginId, out var caps)
 743            ? caps.ToArray()
 744            : Array.Empty<KnowledgeCapability>();
 745    }
 746
 747    /// <summary>
 748    /// Gets all plugins that have a specific capability.
 749    /// </summary>
 750    /// <param name="capability">The capability to search for.</param>
 751    /// <returns>Array of plugin IDs.</returns>
 752    public string[] GetPluginsWithCapability(KnowledgeCapability capability)
 753    {
 754        ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(capability);
 755
 756        return _capabilityToPlugins.TryGetValue(capability.CapabilityId, out var plugins)
 757            ? plugins.ToArray()
 758            : Array.Empty<string>();
 759    }
 760
 761    /// <summary>
 762    /// Gets all plugins that have a capability matching the given ID.
 763    /// </summary>
 764    /// <param name="capabilityId">The capability ID to search for.</param>
 765    /// <returns>Array of plugin IDs.</returns>
 766    public string[] GetPluginsWithCapability(string capabilityId)
 767    {
 768        ArgumentException.ThrowIfNullOrEmpty(capabilityId);
 769
 770        return _capabilityToPlugins.TryGetValue(capabilityId, out var plugins)
 771            ? plugins.ToArray()
 772            : Array.Empty<string>();
 773    }
 774
 775    /// <summary>
 776    /// Updates the capabilities for a plugin.
 777    /// </summary>
 778    /// <param name="pluginId">The plugin ID.</param>
 779    /// <param name="capabilities">The new capabilities.</param>
 780    public void UpdateCapabilities(string pluginId, KnowledgeCapability[] capabilities)
 781    {
 782        ArgumentException.ThrowIfNullOrEmpty(pluginId);
 783        ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(capabilities);
 784
 785        lock (_updateLock)
 786        {
 787            // Remove old mappings
 788            if (_matrix.TryGetValue(pluginId, out var oldCaps))
 789            {
 790                foreach (var oldCap in oldCaps)
 791                {
 792                    if (_capabilityToPlugins.TryGetValue(oldCap.CapabilityId, out var plugins))
 793                    {
 794                        plugins.Remove(pluginId);
 795                    }
 796                }
 797            }
 798
 799            // Add new mappings
 800            _matrix[pluginId] = new HashSet<KnowledgeCapability>(capabilities, new CapabilityComparer());
 801
 802            foreach (var cap in capabilities)
 803            {
 804                if (!_capabilityToPlugins.TryGetValue(cap.CapabilityId, out var plugins))
 805                {
 806                    plugins = new HashSet<string>(StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase);
 807                    _capabilityToPlugins[cap.CapabilityId] = plugins;
 808                }
 809                plugins.Add(pluginId);
 810            }
 811        }
 812    }
 813
 814    /// <summary>
 815    /// Removes a plugin from the matrix.
 816    /// </summary>
 817    /// <param name="pluginId">The plugin ID to remove.</param>
 818    public void RemovePlugin(string pluginId)
 819    {
 820        ArgumentException.ThrowIfNullOrEmpty(pluginId);
 821
 822        lock (_updateLock)
 823        {
 824            if (_matrix.TryRemove(pluginId, out var caps))
 825            {
 826                foreach (var cap in caps)
 827                {
 828                    if (_capabilityToPlugins.TryGetValue(cap.CapabilityId, out var plugins))
 829                    {
 830                        plugins.Remove(pluginId);
 831                    }
 832                }
 833            }
 834        }
 835    }
 836
 837    /// <summary>
 838    /// Gets all registered plugin IDs.
 839    /// </summary>
 840    public IReadOnlyCollection<string> AllPluginIds => _matrix.Keys.ToArray();
 841
 842    /// <summary>
 843    /// Gets all registered capability IDs.
 844    /// </summary>
 845    public IReadOnlyCollection<string> AllCapabilityIds => _capabilityToPlugins.Keys.ToArray();
 846
 847    /// <summary>
 848    /// Searches for capabilities matching a pattern.
 849    /// </summary>
 850    /// <param name="pattern">The search pattern (supports * wildcard).</param>
 851    /// <returns>Matching capabilities.</returns>
 852    public IEnumerable<KnowledgeCapability> SearchCapabilities(string pattern)
 853    {
 854        ArgumentException.ThrowIfNullOrEmpty(pattern);
 855
 856        var regex = new Regex("^" + Regex.Escape(pattern).Replace("\\*", ".*") + "$", RegexOptions.IgnoreCase);
 857
 858        return _matrix.Values
 859            .SelectMany(caps => caps)
 860            .Where(cap => regex.IsMatch(cap.CapabilityId))
 861            .Distinct(new CapabilityComparer());
 862    }
 863
 864    private sealed class CapabilityComparer : IEqualityComparer<KnowledgeCapability>
 865    {
 866        public bool Equals(KnowledgeCapability? x, KnowledgeCapability? y)
 867        {
 868            if (ReferenceEquals(x, y)) return true;
 869            if (x is null || y is null) return false;
 870            return string.Equals(x.CapabilityId, y.CapabilityId, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase);
 871        }
 872
 873        public int GetHashCode(KnowledgeCapability obj)
 874        {
 875            return StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase.GetHashCode(obj.CapabilityId);
 876        }
 877    }
 878}

 998    /// <summary>

 1000    /// </summary>
 1001    /// <param name="requirements">The context requirements.</param>
 1002    /// <param name="ct">Cancellation token.</param>
 1003    /// <returns>The built system context.</returns>
 1004    public async Task<SystemContext> BuildContextAsync(ContextRequirements requirements, CancellationToken ct = default)
 1005    {
 1006        ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(requirements);
 1007
 1008        var contextBuilder = new StringBuilder();
 1009        var includedKnowledge = new List<KnowledgeObject>();
 1010        var excludedIds = new List<string>();
 1011        var currentTokenCount = 0;
 1012
 1013        // Get current state
 1014        var state = await _stateAggregator.GetCurrentStateAsync(ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 1015        if (requirements.IncludeState)
 1016        {
 1017            var stateText = FormatState(state);
 1018            var stateTokens = EstimateTokens(stateText);
 1019            if (currentTokenCount + stateTokens <= requirements.MaxTokens)
 1020            {
 1021                contextBuilder.AppendLine("## Current System State");
 1022                contextBuilder.AppendLine(stateText);
 1023                contextBuilder.AppendLine();
 1024                currentTokenCount += stateTokens;
 1025            }
 1026        }
 1027
 1028        // Get commands
 1029        var commands = new List<CommandDefinition>();
 1030        if (requirements.IncludeCommands)
 1031        {
 1032            commands.AddRange(_commandRegistry.GetAllCommands());
 1033            var commandsText = FormatCommands(commands);
 1034            var commandsTokens = EstimateTokens(commandsText);
 1035            if (currentTokenCount + commandsTokens <= requirements.MaxTokens)
 1036            {
 1037                contextBuilder.AppendLine("## Available Commands");
 1038                contextBuilder.AppendLine(commandsText);
 1039                contextBuilder.AppendLine();
 1040                currentTokenCount += commandsTokens;
 1041            }
 1042        }
 1043
 1044        // Select relevant domains based on query
 1045        var relevantDomainsList = requirements.RequiredDomains.Count > 0
 1046            ? requirements.RequiredDomains.ToList()
 1047            : (await _domainSelector.SelectDomainsAsync(requirements.Query ?? string.Empty, ct).ConfigureAwait(false)).T
 1048
 1049        // Get all knowledge
 1050        var aggregatedKnowledge = await _aggregator.GetAllKnowledgeAsync(ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 1051

 1053        var prioritizedKnowledge = aggregatedKnowledge.AllKnowledge
 1054            .Where(k => relevantDomainsList.Count == 0 || relevantDomainsList.Any(d => k.Topic.StartsWith(d, StringCompa
 1055            .OrderByDescending(k => k.Confidence)
 1056            .ThenByDescending(k => k.Timestamp)
 1057            .ToList();
 1058
 1059        contextBuilder.AppendLine("## Domain Knowledge");
 1060
 1061        foreach (var knowledge in prioritizedKnowledge)
 1062        {
 1063            var knowledgeText = FormatKnowledge(knowledge);
 1064            var knowledgeTokens = EstimateTokens(knowledgeText);
 1065
 1066            if (currentTokenCount + knowledgeTokens <= requirements.MaxTokens)
 1067            {

 1069                includedKnowledge.Add(knowledge);
 1070                currentTokenCount += knowledgeTokens;
 1071            }
 1072            else
 1073            {
 1074                excludedIds.Add(knowledge.Id);
 1075            }
 1076        }
 1077
 1078        return new SystemContext
 1079        {
 1080            ContextPrompt = contextBuilder.ToString(),
 1081            AvailableCommands = commands,
 1082            CurrentState = state,
 1083            IncludedKnowledge = includedKnowledge,
 1084            TokenCount = currentTokenCount,
 1085            ExcludedKnowledgeIds = excludedIds
 1086        };
 1087    }

 1149{
 1150    private readonly ConcurrentDictionary<string, CachedDomainSelection> _cache = new(StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase);
 1151    private readonly TimeSpan _cacheExpiration = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10);
 1152    private readonly KnowledgeAggregator _aggregator;

 1163    /// <summary>
 1164    /// Selects relevant domains for a given query.
 1165    /// </summary>
 1166    /// <param name="query">The query text.</param>
 1167    /// <param name="ct">Cancellation token.</param>
 1168    /// <returns>Collection of relevant domain names.</returns>
 1169    public async Task<IEnumerable<string>> SelectDomainsAsync(string query, CancellationToken ct = default)
 1170    {
 1171        if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(query))
 1172        {
 1173            return await GetAllDomainsAsync(ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 1174        }
 1175
 1176        // Check cache
 1177        var cacheKey = NormalizeQuery(query);
 1178        if (_cache.TryGetValue(cacheKey, out var cached) && !cached.IsExpired(_cacheExpiration))
 1179        {
 1180            return cached.Domains;
 1181        }
 1182
 1183        // Get all knowledge to extract domains
 1184        var aggregated = await _aggregator.GetAllKnowledgeAsync(ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 1185        var allTopics = aggregated.ByTopic.Keys.ToList();
 1186
 1187        // Simple keyword matching for domain selection
 1188        var queryWords = query.ToLowerInvariant().Split(new[] { ' ', ',', '.', '!', '?' }, StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmpt
 1189        var matchedDomains = new List<(string Domain, int Score)>();
 1190
 1191        foreach (var topic in allTopics)
 1192        {
 1193            var score = CalculateRelevanceScore(topic, queryWords);
 1194            if (score > 0)
 1195            {
 1196                matchedDomains.Add((topic, score));
 1197            }
 1198        }
 1199
 1200        var selectedDomains = matchedDomains
 1201            .OrderByDescending(d => d.Score)
 1202            .Take(10)
 1203            .Select(d => d.Domain)
 1204            .ToList();
 1205
 1206        // Cache the result
 1207        _cache[cacheKey] = new CachedDomainSelection
 1208        {
 1209            Domains = selectedDomains,
 1210            CachedAt = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow
 1211        };
 1212
 1213        return selectedDomains;
 1214    }

 1219        return aggregated.ByTopic.Keys;

 1227    private static int CalculateRelevanceScore(string topic, string[] queryWords)
 1228    {
 1229        var topicLower = topic.ToLowerInvariant();
 1230        var score = 0;
 1231
 1232        foreach (var word in queryWords)
 1233        {
 1234            if (topicLower.Contains(word))
 1235            {
 1236                score += 10;
 1237            }
 1238            else if (word.Length >= 3)
 1239            {
 1240                // Partial match for longer words
 1241                var topicParts = topicLower.Split('.');
 1242                foreach (var part in topicParts)
 1243                {
 1244                    if (part.Contains(word) || word.Contains(part))
 1245                    {
 1246                        score += 5;
 1247                    }
 1248                }
 1249            }
 1250        }
 1251
 1252        return score;
 1253    }

 1450    private void SubscribeToStateUpdates()
 1451    {
 1452        if (_messageBus == null) return;

 1455        var topics = new[]
 1456        {
 1457            "plugin.state.update",
 1458            "connection.state.update",
 1459            "operation.state.update",
 1460            "metric.update"

 1468                _subscriptions.Add(sub);

 1470            catch

 1473            }

 1477    private Task HandleStateUpdateAsync(PluginMessage message)
 1478    {
 1479        switch (message.Type)
 1480        {
 1481            case "plugin.state.update":
 1482                if (message.Payload.TryGetValue("pluginId", out var pluginIdObj) && pluginIdObj is string pluginId)
 1483                {
 1484                    var data = message.Payload
 1485                        .Where(kvp => kvp.Key != "pluginId")
 1486                        .ToDictionary(kvp => kvp.Key, kvp => kvp.Value);
 1487                    UpdatePluginState(pluginId, data);
 1488                }
 1489                break;
 1490
 1491            case "metric.update":
 1492                if (message.Payload.TryGetValue("name", out var nameObj) && nameObj is string name &&
 1493                    message.Payload.TryGetValue("value", out var value))
 1494                {
 1495                    UpdateMetric(name, value);
 1496                }
 1497                break;
 1498        }
 1499
 1500        return Task.CompletedTask;
 1501    }

 1503    private string DetermineOverallHealth()
 1504    {
 1505        // Simple health determination based on available data
 1506        if (_pluginStates.IsEmpty && _activeConnections == 0)
 1507        {
 1508            return "Unknown";
 1509        }
 1510
 1511        var activePlugins = _pluginStates.Values.Count(p => p.IsActive);
 1512        var totalPlugins = _pluginStates.Count;
 1513
 1514        if (totalPlugins == 0)
 1515        {
 1516            return "Healthy";
 1517        }
 1518
 1519        var healthRatio = (double)activePlugins / totalPlugins;
 1520
 1521        return healthRatio switch
 1522        {
 1523            >= 0.9 => "Healthy",
 1524            >= 0.7 => "Degraded",
 1525            >= 0.5 => "Warning",
 1526            _ => "Critical"
 1527        };
 1528    }

 1537        {
 1538            try { sub.Dispose(); } catch { /* ignore */ }
 1539        }

 1667    /// <summary>
 1668    /// Searches for commands matching a query.

 1671    /// <returns>Matching command definitions.</returns>
 1672    public IEnumerable<CommandDefinition> SearchCommands(string query)
 1673    {
 1674        if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(query))
 1675        {
 1676            return _commands.Values;
 1677        }
 1678
 1679        var queryLower = query.ToLowerInvariant();
 1680        var words = queryLower.Split(new[] { ' ' }, StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmptyEntries);
 1681

 1683            .Where(cmd => MatchesQuery(cmd, words))

 1697    }

 1710
 1711    /// <summary>
 1712    /// Gets the total number of registered commands.
 1713    /// </summary>
 1714    public int Count => _commands.Count;
 1715
 1716    private static bool MatchesQuery(CommandDefinition cmd, string[] words)
 1717    {
 1718        var searchText = $"{cmd.Name} {cmd.Description} {cmd.Category ?? ""} {string.Join(" ", cmd.Tags)}".ToLowerInvari
 1719        return words.All(word => searchText.Contains(word));
 1720    }
 1721
 1722    private static int CalculateMatchScore(CommandDefinition cmd, string[] words)
 1723    {
 1724        var score = 0;
 1725        var nameLower = cmd.Name.ToLowerInvariant();
 1726        var descLower = cmd.Description.ToLowerInvariant();
 1727
 1728        foreach (var word in words)
 1729        {
 1730            if (nameLower.Contains(word)) score += 10;
 1731            if (descLower.Contains(word)) score += 5;
 1732            if (cmd.Tags.Any(t => t.ToLowerInvariant().Contains(word))) score += 3;
 1733        }
 1734
 1735        return score;
 1736    }

 1916/// <summary>

 1923    /// <summary>

 1930        _handlers[handler.HandlerName] = handler;

 1933    /// <summary>
 1934    /// Unregisters a knowledge handler.
 1935    /// </summary>

 1943    /// <summary>
 1944    /// Routes a request to an appropriate handler.

 1960    }

 1968    {
 1969        ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(request);
 1970
 1971        return _handlers.Values
 1972            .Where(h => h.CanHandle(request))
 1973            .OrderByDescending(h => h.Priority);
 1974    }

 1976    /// <summary>
 1977    /// Gets the number of registered handlers.

 1986/// <summary>

 1996    /// <summary>

 2006        StateAggregator stateAggregator,

 2008    {
 2009        _router = router ?? throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(router));
 2010        _aggregator = aggregator ?? throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(aggregator));
 2011        _stateAggregator = stateAggregator ?? throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(stateAggregator));

 2013    }
 2014
 2015    /// <summary>
 2016    /// Executes a knowledge query.
 2017    /// </summary>
 2018    /// <param name="request">The request to execute.</param>
 2019    /// <param name="ct">Cancellation token.</param>
 2020    /// <returns>The query response.</returns>
 2021    public async Task<KnowledgeQueryResponse> ExecuteQueryAsync(KnowledgeQueryRequest request, CancellationToken ct = de
 2022    {
 2023        ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(request);
 2024
 2025        var sw = Stopwatch.StartNew();
 2026
 2027        try
 2028        {
 2029            // Validate request
 2030            var validationError = ValidateRequest(request);
 2031            if (validationError != null)
 2032            {
 2033                return KnowledgeQueryResponse.Fail(request.RequestId, validationError, "VALIDATION_ERROR");
 2034            }
 2035
 2036            // Route to handler
 2037            var handler = await _router.RouteAsync(request, ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 2038
 2039            if (handler != null)
 2040            {
 2041                return await handler.HandleAsync(request, ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 2042            }
 2043
 2044            // Default handling based on query type
 2045            return request.QueryType switch
 2046            {
 2047                KnowledgeQueryType.Facts => await HandleFactsQueryAsync(request, ct).ConfigureAwait(false),
 2048                KnowledgeQueryType.State => await HandleStateQueryAsync(request, ct).ConfigureAwait(false),
 2049                KnowledgeQueryType.Commands => HandleCommandsQuery(request),
 2050                KnowledgeQueryType.Capabilities => await HandleCapabilitiesQueryAsync(request, ct).ConfigureAwait(false)
 2051                _ => KnowledgeQueryResponse.Fail(request.RequestId, $"Unsupported query type: {request.QueryType}", "UNS
 2052            };
 2053        }
 2054        catch (OperationCanceledException)
 2055        {
 2056            return KnowledgeQueryResponse.Fail(request.RequestId, "Query was cancelled", "CANCELLED", sw.Elapsed);
 2057        }
 2058        catch (Exception ex)
 2059        {
 2060            return KnowledgeQueryResponse.Fail(request.RequestId, ex.Message, "INTERNAL_ERROR", sw.Elapsed);
 2061        }
 2062    }

 2064    private static string? ValidateRequest(KnowledgeQueryRequest request)
 2065    {
 2066        if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(request.Query))
 2067        {
 2068            return "Query cannot be empty";
 2069        }
 2070
 2071        if (request.Timeout <= TimeSpan.Zero)
 2072        {
 2073            return "Timeout must be positive";
 2074        }
 2075
 2076        return null;
 2077    }
 2078
 2079    private async Task<KnowledgeQueryResponse> HandleFactsQueryAsync(KnowledgeQueryRequest request, CancellationToken ct
 2080    {
 2081        var aggregated = await _aggregator.GetAllKnowledgeAsync(ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 2082
 2083        var queryLower = request.Query.ToLowerInvariant();
 2084        var matchingKnowledge = aggregated.AllKnowledge
 2085            .Where(k => k.Description?.ToLowerInvariant().Contains(queryLower) == true ||
 2086                        k.Topic.ToLowerInvariant().Contains(queryLower))
 2087            .Take(20)
 2088            .ToList();
 2089
 2090        return KnowledgeQueryResponse.Ok(request.RequestId, matchingKnowledge);
 2091    }
 2092
 2093    private async Task<KnowledgeQueryResponse> HandleStateQueryAsync(KnowledgeQueryRequest request, CancellationToken ct
 2094    {
 2095        var state = await _stateAggregator.GetCurrentStateAsync(ct).ConfigureAwait(false);
 2096        return KnowledgeQueryResponse.Ok(request.RequestId, state);
 2097    }
 2098
 2099    private KnowledgeQueryResponse HandleCommandsQuery(KnowledgeQueryRequest request)
 2100    {
 2101        var commands = string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(request.Query)
 2102            ? _commandRegistry.GetAllCommands().ToList()
 2103            : _commandRegistry.SearchCommands(request.Query).ToList();
 2104
 2105        return KnowledgeQueryResponse.Ok(request.RequestId, commands);
 2106    }
 2107
 2108    private async Task<KnowledgeQueryResponse> HandleCapabilitiesQueryAsync(KnowledgeQueryRequest request, CancellationT
 2109    {
